	<Title>
		Winter workout tip: Head into the wind
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;When you begin an outdoor winter workout, head into the wind. You&apos;ll be less likely to get chilled at the end of your workout, when you may be sweaty, if you return with the wind at your back.&lt;/p&gt;
